-- allium: 3
-- specs/cuda-native-dispatch/calibrated_dispatch_framework.allium
--
-- Status: PLACEHOLDER. Bound by PHASE_CUDA_NATIVE_DISPATCH.md
-- commit C0 (calibration framework). This is the FOUNDATIONAL spec
-- of the phase — every other calibrated-op spec composes with this
-- one.
--
-- Scope: the ggml_cuda_calibrate() framework. At context init, the
-- framework probes each registered op at five payload sizes
-- {0, 1MB, 10MB, 100MB, 1GB} and records the smallest bucket where
-- the alt-strategy's p95 latency is less than the default-
-- strategy's p50 latency (the "conservative crossover"). If no
-- crossover is found in the probe range, the threshold is
-- SIZE_MAX (alt-strategy never fires). The threshold table is
-- cached to disk at ~/.cache/ggml/cuda-calibration-{gpu_uuid_hash}
-- .json and reloaded on subsequent context inits when the
-- (gpu_uuid, cuda_version, ggml_version) cache_key matches.
--
-- Why this spec exists: the user directive 2026-05-27 made size-
-- adaptive dispatch the default pattern for the phase. Hardcoding
-- thresholds for one specific hardware (xeon's 2× Quadro RTX 6000
-- + NV2) would be fragile; the same binary on different hardware
-- would pick the wrong strategy. Calibration adapts at runtime.
-- This spec binds the framework's determinism: for a fixed
-- (gpu_uuid, cuda_version, ggml_version) tuple, calibration
-- returns the SAME threshold across processes (modulo quantization
-- absorbing minor variance).
--
-- Includes:
--   - External entity for the calibration framework
--     (CalibrationTable, OpId, Threshold, ProbeResult, CacheFile).
--   - Enumeration of registered ops:
--     {REDUCE_CROSS_DEVICE, MATMUL_STREAM_SPLIT, PEER_COPY,
--      GRAPH_CAPTURE}.
--   - Enumeration of quantization buckets:
--     {0, 1MB, 10MB, 100MB, 1GB, SIZE_MAX}.
--   - Contract ProbeIsDeterministic — for a fixed input and
--     hardware, probe() returns (p50, p95) values that quantize to
--     the same bucket across runs.
--   - Contract CacheLoadIdempotent — calibrate(ctx) writes cache,
--     calibrate(ctx') on a fresh context with matching cache_key
--     loads thresholds bit-identical to the writer.
--   - Contract ThresholdQuantized — every threshold[op] is in
--     {0, 1MB, 10MB, 100MB, 1GB, SIZE_MAX}.
--   - Contract DispatchIsPureFunction — the dispatch decision at
--     a calibrated op site is a pure function of (op_id, payload_
--     bytes, threshold[op_id]).
--
-- CODE REFS (post-C0):
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/calibration.h
--   ik_llama.cpp/ggml/src/ggml-cuda/calibration.cu
--   ggml_backend_cuda_context.{calibration_table}  field added
--   ~/.cache/ggml/cuda-calibration-{key}.json      cache file
--
-- TBD: fill content when C0 lands. The framework determinism is
-- bound by test-cuda-calibration-framework.cpp.

allium 3

